article.headline: Dayton 81, Tennessee Tech 60
article.story: DAYTON, Ohio (AP) -- Brian Roberts scored 28 points to lead Dayton to an 81-60 win over Tennessee Tech on Friday night. The Flyers (1-0) trailed 16-14 with 10 minutes to play in the first half, but Roberts hit a 3-pointer to make it 17-16 and start a 17-4 run to give Dayton control. The Golden Eagles (0-1) got no closer than eight the rest of the game. Dayton forced 24 turnovers, leading to 21 points, and held Tennessee Tech to 36 percent shooting. Dayton shot 56 percent from the floor and scored 36 points in the paint, but the Flyers missed 12 free throws. Monty Scott had 16 points for Dayton and Warren Williams had 10 points and 11 assists. Derek Stribling scored 16 points for Tennessee Tech. Milone Clark and Anthony Fisher each added 10.
